Package: wg-ddns-endpoint-monitor
Version: 1.1.0-2
Section: net
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: bash, wireguard-tools, systemd, libc-bin, util-linux
Maintainer: netplus <netplusplus@outlook.com>
Homepage: https://github.com/netplus/wg-ddns-endpoint-monitor
Description: Monitor DDNS-backed WireGuard peer hostnames and refresh stale runtime endpoints
 A timer-driven oneshot monitor that inspects WireGuard peer Endpoint hostnames,
 checks handshake age, detects DNS/IP changes, and refreshes stale runtime endpoints with wg set.
 .
 It supports automatic discovery from /etc/wireguard/*.conf and optional explicit
 endpoint mappings via /etc/wg-ddns-endpoint-monitor/endpoints.conf.
